# feature-wise percentage of missing values present in the data
def find_missing(df):
    null_percentage=[{col : df[col].isnull().sum()*100/len(df)} for col in df.columns]
    for x in null_percentage:
        for k,v in x.items():
            print("Column name: {0} ; missing percentage : {1}".format(k,v))

3. Model Training & Evaluation using Neural Network [13 Marks]¶

A. Design a Neural Network to train a classifier. [3 Marks]¶

In [44]:
from keras.models import Sequential # Forward prop
from keras.layers import Dense, Activation, LeakyReLU
from keras import optimizers
In [45]:
def create_model(lr,batch_size):  
    np.random.seed(100)
    nn_classifier_model = Sequential()

    # Input Layer :
    nn_classifier_model.add(Dense(128, kernel_initializer='he_normal',input_dim = X_train_s.shape[1], activation='relu'))

    # Hidden Layers :
    nn_classifier_model.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    nn_classifier_model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))

    nn_classifier_model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    nn_classifier_model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))

    nn_classifier_model.add(Dense(16, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    nn_classifier_model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))

    # Output Layer :
    nn_classifier_model.add(Dense(9, kernel_initializer='he_normal',activation='softmax'))

    # Compile :
    optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr)
    nn_classifier_model.compile(loss='mean_absolute_error', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['accuracy'])
    nn_classifier_model.summary()
    return nn_classifier_model

D. Design new architecture/update existing architecture in attempt to improve the performance of the model. [2 Marks]¶

In [51]:
def updated_model(lr,batch_size):  
    np.random.seed(100)
    nn_classifier_model1 = Sequential()

    # Input Layer :
    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dense(128, kernel_initializer='he_normal',input_dim = X_train_s.shape[1], activation='relu'))
    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dropout(0.2))

    # Hidden Layers :
    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='he_normal',activation='relu'))
    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dropout(0.2))

    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='he_normal',activation='relu'))
    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dropout(0.2))

    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dense(16, kernel_initializer='he_normal',activation='relu'))
    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dropout(0.2))


    # Output Layer :
    nn_classifier_model1.add(Dense(9, kernel_initializer='he_normal',activation='softmax'))

    # Compile :
    optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr)
    nn_classifier_model1.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['accuracy'])
    nn_classifier_model1.summary()
    return nn_classifier_model1

3. Model Training & Evaluation using Neural Network [12 Marks]¶

A. Design a Neural Network to train a classifier. [3 Marks]¶

In [83]:
# create the nn classifier model for SVHN data
num_classes=num_class_train
def create_svhn_nn_model(lr,batch_size):  
    np.random.seed(100)
    svhn_nn_model = Sequential()

    # The Input Layer :
    svhn_nn_model.add(Dense(256,input_dim = X_train.shape[1], activation='relu'))

    # The Hidden Layers :
    svhn_nn_model.add(Dense(128,activation='relu'))
    svhn_nn_model.add(Dense(64,activation='relu'))
    svhn_nn_model.add(Dense(32,activation='relu'))

    # The Output Layer :
    svhn_nn_model.add(Dense(num_classes,activation='softmax'))

    # Compile the network :
    optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr)
    svhn_nn_model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['accuracy'])
    svhn_nn_model.summary()
    return svhn_nn_model

Observation:¶

The Street View House Number (SVHN) dataset has 10 classes representing the image data for digits 0-9.

Neural Network classifier model with 1 input layer, 3 hidden layers and 1 output layer was built using relu activation function.

With the best suitable parameters of Learning Rate: 0.001, Batch size: 300 , Epochs :100 the NN classifier model gave the below results:

  • Accuracy in training dataset = 89.91%
  • Accuracy in test dataset = 82.69%
  • Loss in training dataset = 31.54%
  • Loss in test dataset = 66.96%

Conclusion: Model Training accuracy of 89.91% and Test accuracy of 82.69% is the optimized model that was built for this SVHN dataset.¶
